## **2️⃣ Lab 1 Commands Reference (Markdown / Copyable)**

```markdown
# Lab 1 — Command Reference

## Stop and clean Apache
```bash
sudo systemctl stop httpd
sudo pkill -f httpd
Check processes using port 80
bash
Copy code
sudo lsof -i :80
sudo netstat -tulnp | grep :80
Backup default Apache config files
bash
Copy code
sudo mv /etc/httpd/conf.d/welcome.conf /etc/httpd/conf.d/welcome.conf.bak
sudo mv /etc/httpd/conf.d/ssl.conf /etc/httpd/conf.d/ssl.conf.bak
Edit main Apache config
bash
Copy code
sudo vi /etc/httpd/conf/httpd.conf
Ensure only one Listen directive:

apache
Copy code
Listen 0.0.0.0:80
Restart Apache
bash
Copy code
sudo systemctl start httpd
sudo systemctl status httpd
Verify Apache is listening on IPv4 port 80
bash
Copy code
sudo lsof -i :80
curl http://127.0.0.1
Check Linux firewall (if needed)
bash
Copy code
sudo systemctl status firewalld
sudo systemctl stop firewalld  # for testing only
sudo iptables -L -n
Network troubleshooting
bash
Copy code
ping <Elastic-IP>      # Check connectivity from external PC
telnet <Elastic-IP> 80 # Test port reachability
